es to deterministically ordered JSON for consistent hashing and digital signatures per JCS <a href=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8785\">RFC8785</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-04T05:38:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"YuzheSHI/awesome-agi-cocosci","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h4>Dual-Coding Theory</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://bilab.bnu.edu.cn/paper/2018/Wang_2018_Cerebral_Cortex.pdf\">Organizational Principles of Abstract Words in the Human Brain</a> - <em><strong>Cerebral Cortex</strong></em>, 2018. [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?oi=bibs&#x26;hl=en&#x26;cluster=15272192531353715481\">All Versions</a>].</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-04T02:25:43.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"YuzheSHI/awesome-agi-cocosci","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h4>Neural-Symbolic AI</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cs.nju.edu.cn/zhouzh/zhouzh.files/publication/aaai17lasin.pdf\">Combining Logical Abduction and Statistical Induction: Discovering Written Primitives with Human Knowledge</a> - <em><strong>AAAI'17</strong></em>, 2017. [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?cluster=14477085725208589393&#x26;hl=en&#x26;as_sdt=0,5\">All Versions</a>].</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-04T02:25:43.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dive-into-machine-learning/dive-into-machine-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Explore another notebook</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Series of notebooks:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>2022:</strong> <a href=\"https://github.com/rasbt/machine-learning-book\"><code>rasbt/machine-learning-book</code></a> — notebooks from <a href=\"https://sebastianraschka.com/blog/2022/ml-pytorch-book.html\"><em>Machine Learning with PyTorch and Scikit-Learn</em> by Sebastian Raschka, Yuxi (Hayden) Liu, and Vahid Mirjalili</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-04T01:39:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dive-into-machine-learning/dive-into-machine-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>More ways to \"Dive into Machine Learning\"</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Courses by cloud vendors. These are usually high quality content but steer you heavily to use vendor-specific tools/services. To avoid getting locked into vendor specifics, you can make sure you're learning from other resources as well.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/microsoft/ML-For-Beginners\"><code>microsoft/ML-For-Beginners</code></a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/microsoft/Data-Science-For-Beginners\"><code>microsoft/Data-Science-For-Beginners</code></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/machine-learning/crash-course/\">Machine Learning Crash Course from Google</a> (<a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/training/machinelearning-ai\">more of their options</a>)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/machine-learning/mlu/\">Amazon AWS</a> (<a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/machine-learning/learn/\">more of their options</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-04T01:39:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hangtwenty/dive-into-machine-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Explore another notebook</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Series of notebooks:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>2022:</strong> <a href=\"https://github.com/rasbt/machine-learning-book\"><code>rasbt/machine-learning-book</code></a> — notebooks from <a href=\"https://sebastianraschka.com/blog/2022/ml-pytorch-book.html\"><em>Machine Learning with PyTorch and Scikit-Learn</em> by Sebastian Raschka, Yuxi (Hayden) Liu, and Vahid Mirjalili</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-04T01:39:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"hangtwenty/dive-into-machine-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>More ways to \"Dive into Machine Learning\"</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Courses by cloud vendors. These are usually high quality content but steer you heavily to use vendor-specific tools/services. To avoid getting locked into vendor specifics, you can make sure you're learning from other resources as well.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/microsoft/ML-For-Beginners\"><code>microsoft/ML-For-Beginners</code></a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/microsoft/Data-Science-For-Beginners\"><code>microsoft/Data-Science-For-Beginners</code></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/machine-learning/crash-course/\">Machine Learning Crash Course from Google</a> (<a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/training/machinelearning-ai\">more of their options</a>)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/machine-learning/mlu/\">Amazon AWS</a> (<a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/machine-learning/learn/\">more of their options</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-04T01:39:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"awesome-css-group/awesome-css","categoryHTML":"<h2>Reset and Normalize</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ruilisi/css-checker\">CSS Checker</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ruilisi/css-checker\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">535</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":535,\"repo\":\"ruilisi/css-checker\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Find and Reduce Similar &#x26; Duplicated CSS Scripts.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-04T00:56:34.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1646352000000,"to":1646438399999,"previousId":"2022-03-05","nextId":"2022-03-03","nextName":"Mar 3rd, 2022","previousName":"Mar 5th, 2022"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}